briefTitle: Evidence-based Stimulation Trial With Human rFSH in Europe and Rest of World 2
officialTitle: A Controlled, Assessor-blind, Parallel Groups, Multicentre, Multinational Trial Evaluating the Immunogenicity of FE 999049 in Repeated Cycles of Controlled Ovarian Stimulation in Women Undergoing an Assisted Reproductive Technology Programme
summary: This trial investigates the immunogenicity of FE 999049 in repeated cycles.

primaryOutcome.measure: Proportion (Percentage) of Subjects With Treatment-induced Anti-Follicle-Stimulating Hormone (FSH) Antibodies After up to Two Repeated Controlled Ovarian Stimulation Cycles
primaryOutcome.timeFrame: Stimulation day 1, 7-10 days after last FE 999049 or GONAL-F dose and 21-28 days after last FE 999049 or GONAL-F dose
